<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99277319599424></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99277319599424><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=4710&mid=99277319599424>Cheaters sometimes win....</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=56112><span id= >Reegor</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>46 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jun 17th 6:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I was at the Minneapolis Fan Faire and was participating in the real life quest.  The prizes where staffs/swords of the gathering.  It was not stated in the rules, but the use of cell phones and walkie talkies (ect) got you disqualified (there was a guy taking down names).  We diddn't cheat.  We did better than everyone we talked to.  We where a few mins fom finishing but we had to turn it in due to the time limit.  One other team we talked to did as well as us but they used walkie talkies.  We thaught we had it in the bag.  Wrong.  That group diddn't win, but another that had been using walkie talkies did win.  Some just slip through the cracks.  Lucky bastards.  If you guys read this, I hope you're pleased with your weapons.  Cheaters never win?  Cheaters sometimes win, apparently.<br>&nbsp;<br>Reegor Mortees &lt;The Keepers&gt;<br>51st heretic<br>E'Ci<br>Boo Boo is my lengthy motsa ball.</td></tr>
